Species: The genus is represented by four species (
Devriese, 2014
):
U. nodulosus (Fieber, 1853 )
in Portugal (
Fig. 4
), SW Spain and North Africa (
Devriese, 1996
);
U. transsylvanicus (
Bazyluk & Kis, 1960
)
in Slovenia , Croatia and Romania (discussed below),
U. pseudodepressus
Ingrisch, 2006
in Nepal (Bheri province) (
Ingrisch, 2006
) and
U. gibberosus (
Wang & Zheng, 1993
)
in East China (Anhui) (
Wang & Zheng, 1993
).

Generic diagnosis. Paranota with only one lobe, tegmenula and alae rudimentary, hind femora knees with deep incision (
Devriese, 1996
).
